=Description=

Auki Network:

"Spatial computing is the bridge between the digital and physical realms, a transformative technology that enables digital devices to understand and interact with the world around us. It is the cornerstone of the next internet evolution, where artificial intelligence (AI) steps out of the confines of the screen to become an active participant in our daily lives and engage with the tangible world.

It is a paradigm shift that will redefine how we experience reality, enhancing our capabilities and reshaping our interactions with both the environment and the machines that serve us. It is the evolution of AI's sensory perception, allowing it to grasp and navigate our physical environment.

By facilitating a universal, privacy-focused exchange of spatial data, the posemesh stands as a beacon for the future of AI development and application, ensuring that the digital entities we create can coexist and interact within our world in meaningful ways.

The posemesh is a spatial computing protocol that is universal in its application but also prioritizes user privacy. This approach enables a collaborative spatial data exchange that is essential for the development of AI and is truly integrated with our physical surroundings, making the posemesh an indispensable component for spatial computing.'

(https://www.aukilabs.com/community/news/introducing-the-posemesh-spatial-computings-foundational-layer?)


